practitioner.about:
Dr. Ali Abdelmaboud Hassan Ali is a skilled Orthopaedic Specialist in the Department of Orthopaedics at Medcare Medical Centre. He completed his MBBS and MD in Orthopaedics from Al-Azhar University in Cairo, Egypt. He is a member of the Egyptian Orthopaedic Association, the Egyptian Group of Arthroscopy and Sports Medicine, the Egyptian Group of Hip and Pelvis, the AO Foundation of Orthopaedics, Switzerland and the European Trauma Organization.

Dr. Ali has spent over two decades working in several countries, including Egypt, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait and the UAE. He commenced his career in Egypt at the Al-Hussein University Hospital and later served at the Hospital of the Police Academy and the Agouza Police Hospital, all in Cairo. He then moved to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to join the Dammam Central Hospital as an Orthopaedic Specialist. Later, he worked at the Razi and Jahra Hospitals in Kuwait.  Subsequently, he relocated to the UAE, where he gained invaluable experience as an Orthopaedic Surgeon at the Khorfakkan Hospital in Sharjah, the Elaj Medical Center in Ajman, the Emirates European Hospital in Sharjah, the Dr. Sulaiman Al Habib Hospital, The Green Life Clinic in Dubai, Al Hana Modern Medical Centre and Orthosports Medical Centre.

Dr. Ali’s expertise covers arthroscopy, arthroplasty, sports injuries, work-related injuries, general trauma management for adults and children, treatment of all orthopaedic conditions, including spine problems and providing epidural injection for pain management. He administers all types of injections, including PRP, local and hyaluronic material.

During his spare time, he likes to keep fit by jogging, swimming, and playing Tennis and Squash. He speaks both Arabic and English.
